    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-06-24T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-06-24T23:00:00-05:00" n="240"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d240">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.85/642: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lane</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-06-25T00:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 25, 1942—midnight</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>724. Your 832, June 23, 7 p.m. With reference to the suggested form of transfer
                    the War Shipping Administration prefers that the transfer be made directly from
                    the Colombian Government to the United States represented by the War Shipping
                    Administrator. If determination to make transfer on these terms is final, War
                    Shipping Administration is prepared to send crews as soon as it can arrange
                    transportation by air.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
